Bank of America Corp.  hired Robert Sachs from  UBS AG (UBSN)  to run a global team that helps hedge funds
raise money from pension plans and other investors.  Sachs will join as global head of capital introductions and
strategy, reporting to Jon Yalmokas, head of the U.S. prime
brokerage, Stu Hendel, global head of the financing products,
said in a memo to employees obtained by  Bloomberg News . He will
be based in New York and start in coming months, Hendel wrote.  John Yiannacopoulos, a spokesman for the Charlotte, North
Carolina-based bank, confirmed the contents of the document and
declined to comment further.  Sachs was global head of capital introductions for the last
four years at UBS and previously worked at New York-based
investment firm Constellar Capital Management, where he was a
founding member. Before that, he worked at Olympia Capital
Management and Credit Suisse Group AG, according to the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
